        <h2 id="name">Recipe #1 Eggs</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 5 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 1 </li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Eggs</td>
                    <td>2</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Oil</td>
                    <td>30 ml</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Take frying pan, eggs and oil.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Pour vegetable oil into a clean skillet and heat.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Crack the eggs and pour them into the skillet, being careful not to damage the yolk.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Season with salt to taste and cook for 2-3 minutes. Using a spatula, gently transfer the eggs to a plate and serve.
</p>
        
        
    <p class="sourrce"><em>Source: <a href="https://povar.ru/recipes/yaichnica_obychnaya-53132.html">Eggs recipe</a></em></p>
    <h2 id="name">Recipe #2 Porridge</h2>
    <ul>
            <li>Time: 25 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 3 </li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Rice</td>
                    <td>1 glass</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Milk</td>
                    <td>4 glass</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sugar</td>
                    <td>1 spoon</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> Rinse the rice with warm water, pour into boiling water, cook for 8-10 minutes, stirring from time to time.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Place the rice on a sieve and let the water drain. Heat the milk in a 2 liter saucepan. Pour rice into milk, stir and cook.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Add sugar before switching off.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Wrap the porridge with a towel for 5-10 minutes.Before serving, milk rice porridge is seasoned with butter.
</p>
        
        
    <p class="sourrce"><em>Source: <a href="https://www.russianfood.com/recipes/recipe.php?rid=7221">Porridge recipe</a></em></p>
    
    <h2 id="name">Recipe #3 Pancakes</h2>
        
        <ul>
            <li>Time: 30 min</li>
            <li>Serves: 4 </li>
        </ul>
        
        <table>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Ingredients</th>
                    <th>Quantity</th>
                </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Milk</td>
                    <td>200 ml</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Flour</td>
                    <td>200 g</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Egg</td>
                    <td>1</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Oil</td>
                    <td>2 tablespoons</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Sugar</td>
                    <td>30 g</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Baking powder</td>
                    <td>5 g</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
        
        <p><strong>Step 1:</strong> In the container in which we will make the dough for pancakes, knock out the egg, add sugar.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 2:</strong> Stir with a mixer or just a whisk until smooth and completely dissolved, add milk and butter, mix.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Sift flour and baking powder into a separate container. We mix everything very thoroughly, I recommend doing this with a whisk, so the result will be better. Add the sifted flour with baking powder to the container with the dough. Stir until smooth.
</p>
        <p><strong>Step 4:</strong> Put the pan on medium heat and heat well. Pour the dough into a hot skillet. Pancakes bake quite quickly, so I recommend pouring the dough for one pancake at a time.
</p>
        
        
    <p class="sourrce"><em>Source: <a href="https://art-lunch.ru/recipe/pankejki_foto/">Pancakes recipe</a></em></p>
    </body>
